Hi,

When an interface, say a.mli, includes a signature, say B.MYSIG
(through "include B.MYSIG"), ocamlbrowser nicely displays in its 3
panes B.MYSIG functions/types/... alongside the ones declared in
a.mli.  However, when one asks the interface of a function/type/... of
B.MYSIG, the beginning of a.mli is displayed.  When b.mli exists, why
not follow the "link" and present the user the corresponding
function/type/... in [the signature MYSIG in] b.mli?

Cheers,
ChriS

